Checklists and scratchpads

When to use
- Multi-file refactors, migrations, repeated errors, or long debugging.

How to use
- Maintain a checklist in-chat or in a small doc file (AI may create one if helpful).
- Keep it short, actionable, and up to date.

Suggested structure
- Goal
- Assumptions
- Checklist (one item per step)
- Findings/decisions
- Verification notes
